.TH "__of_iio_simple_xlate" 9 "__of_iio_simple_xlate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__of_iio_simple_xlate \- translate iiospec to the IIO channel index
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __of_iio_simple_xlate
.BI "(struct iio_dev *indio_dev "  ","
.BI "const struct of_phandle_args *iiospec "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "indio_dev" 12
pointer to the iio_dev structure
.IP "iiospec" 12
IIO specifier as found in the device tree
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is simple translation function, suitable for the most 1:1 mapped
channels in IIO chips. This function performs only one sanity check:
whether IIO index is less than num_channels (that is specified in the
iio_dev).
